steps.description:
Remove any molding above and below the intended opening location. Remove the drywall between those studs indicated from the floor to the ceiling first by scoring the wall with a razor blade (utility knife) along the inside of the studs. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/38/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/38/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

With a hammer or gloved fist, knock out just enough drywall to locate any wires or other obstructions that could be damaged with a saw. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3b/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3b/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Use of a utility knife works surprisingly well on drywall, and will result in the least amount of dust and risk of damaging wires and pipes in the wall space. To use the knife, repeatedly score the wall top to bottom. You do not need to completely penetrate through the drywall—just get through 1/2 to 3/4 of the thickness. A sharp hit on the wall with a gloved fist will break the drywall along the scored line. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f7/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-3Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f7/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-3Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-3Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Alternately, you can saw out the drywall by cutting as close as possible to the side of the studs. Use of hand saws made for drywall will minimize dust. If using a Sawzall or similar, a helper with a vacuum following your cutting path will reduce dust considerably. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a8/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-3Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-3Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a8/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-3Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-3Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Remove the insulation. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b3/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-3Bullet5.jpg/v4-460px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-3Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/b3/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-3Bullet5.jpg/v4-760px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-3Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Remove the center stud(s) if needed to accommodate the AC unit. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d3/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-3Bullet6.jpg/v4-460px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-3Bullet6.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/d3/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-3Bullet6.jpg/v4-760px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-3Bullet6.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

It will be the top of the framework for the opening. Cut two (2 x 4 construction) or three (2 x 6 construction) pieces of the same length from a 2-by. Cut one or two (again, 1 for 2x4 or 2 for 2x6 construction) strips of 1/2" plywood the same size as the 2-bys. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/5b/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-7Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-7Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/5b/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-7Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-7Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Place the plywood strips between the 2-bys and nail or screw together. The completed header thickness should be very close to 3-1/2 or 5-1/2 inches (for 2x4 or 2x6 construction, respectively). {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/80/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-7Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-7Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/8/80/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-7Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-7Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Cut two 2-bys equal to the opening height. Secure them against the existing studs in the space for the unit, by resting on the bottom horizontal support previously installed and nail or screw in place. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/0d/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-7Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-7Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/0/0d/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-7Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-7Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Rest the header on top of the vertical supports installed in the previous step. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/dd/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-7Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-7Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/d/dd/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-7Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-7Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Secure the header by nailing or screwing in place. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/4b/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-7Bullet5.jpg/v4-460px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-7Bullet5.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/4b/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-7Bullet5.jpg/v4-760px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-7Bullet5.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Reinstall the insulation. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3b/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-11Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-11Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3b/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-11Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-11Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Install the drywall. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3d/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-11Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-11Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3d/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-11Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-11Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Tape, mud (joint compound) and sand when dry. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/34/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-11Bullet3.jpg/v4-460px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-11Bullet3.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/34/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-11Bullet3.jpg/v4-760px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-11Bullet3.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Paint wall and reinstall all molding. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a8/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-11Bullet4.jpg/v4-460px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-11Bullet4.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/a/a8/Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-11Bullet4.jpg/v4-760px-Install-an-Inwall-Air-Conditioner-Step-11Bullet4.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}
